title: Rochester man indicted on murder charges
text:
A Rochester man was indicted by a Monroe County grand jury on charges of second-degree murder. Jodeci M. Sinclair, 23, is scheduled to be arraigned at 2 p.m. Friday in front of Monroe County Court Judge Victoria Argento. He is also facing two counts of second-degree criminal possession of a weapon, a felony.
Sinclair is accused of fatally shooting Tyrone Snowden, 24, on Ernst Street in May.
Snowden, who was shot in the leg, died two weeks later from his injuries.
ROCHESTER DEMOCRAT AND CHRONICLE
Arrest made in May homicide
WCLEVELAND@Gannett.com
